pkglist:
	Some necessary/nice packages. These are Debian package names, so they
	might not work for you if you're running something else.
	Usage:
		apt install $(cat pkglist)

xorg.conf.d/:
	Display and input device configs, these go under /etc/.

* Dpi is changed in .Xresources
* Fonts are changed in .Xresources and i3/config
* For the command 'wal' install pywal (pip3 install pywal)
